aptac test suite
================

git-style harness. Each t[0-9]*.sh sources test-lib.sh, which drops fake
pacman/sudo/checkupdates/paccache/pactree/reflector onto PATH. The fakes only
log their argv to a per-script call log; aptac is a wrapper, so the tests assert
"aptac invoked the right underlying command" without touching the real system.

Run (run.sh cd's into t/ for you; scripts source ./test-lib.sh so a single
script or prove must be invoked from inside t/):
    sh t/run.sh                    # all scripts, PASS/FAIL summary
    sh t/run.sh -v                 # also show each body's output
    (cd t && prove ./t[0-9]*.sh)   # TAP via prove, if installed
    (cd t && sh t0200-list.sh)     # a single script

Writing a test:
    test_expect_success 'desc' '
        reset_calls &&
        aptac --no-color <cmd> &&
        grep_call "pacman -Whatever"
    '

Helpers: aptac, reset_calls, grep_call, test_must_fail, test_cmp,
test_when_finished. Stub knobs (env): STUB_ORPHANS, STUB_UPDATES,
STUB_CHECK_RC, STUB_PACMAN_RC. PACMAN_LOCAL points --first/--last at a fixture.
